# Playwright and Sandboxed Execution

Playwright cannot install browsers, spawn a web server, or launch Chromium
inside the default tool sandbox. Agents that invoke Playwright from inside the
sandbox will see confusing, non-deterministic failures such as:

- `browserType.launch: Executable doesn't exist at …/chrome-headless-shell-<n>/…`
- Dev-server start timeouts
- Silent network blocks when Playwright tries to download browser binaries

## Rule

When running any command that may invoke Playwright, **request
`required_permissions: ["all"]`** (or at minimum `["full_network"]` plus write
access to the Playwright browser cache) so the command runs outside the
sandbox.

This applies to, at a minimum:

- `git push` (the `pre-push` lefthook runs
  `test:e2e:section-player:critical`, `test:e2e:item-player:multiple-choice`,
  and `test:e2e:assessment-player`; see `lefthook.yml`).
- Any `bun run test:e2e:*` script.
- `bunx playwright …` / `bun playwright …` (install, test, codegen).
- Playwright scripts invoked from agent helper scripts (`verify-*.mjs`,
  ad-hoc DOM verification scripts, screenshot capture, etc.).
- `bun run test` / `bun test` in packages whose `tests/` directory contains
  `*.spec.ts` Playwright specs (most `packages/*-player/tests/`).

## Practical pattern

```text
required_permissions: ["all"]
```

Prefer `["all"]` for `git push` because the pre-push hook chain also runs
`check:publint` / other scripts that write to caches outside the workspace.

## Why not just retry inside the sandbox

The Playwright browser cache lives in a per-sandbox-session temp directory
(for example
`/var/folders/.../cursor-sandbox-cache/<hash>/playwright/chromium_headless_shell-<n>`).
Running outside the sandbox reuses the shared
`~/Library/Caches/ms-playwright/` cache, which already has the matching
browser version installed, so tests start immediately instead of downloading
a fresh ~90 MB Chromium on every run.

